        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Get plain text from SunAwtCanvas",
        "body": "<p>Since it's impossible to capture text from a java canvas by using standard Windows API functions like <code>GetMessage()<\/code>, I wondered if there is any way to hook the <code>drawText()<\/code> method inside such a java canvas and to capture the text before it's actually have been drawn on the canvas. Does anyone have an idea how to solve this? A solution written in java would also be accepted. Any suggestion would be nice, thank you.<\/p>\n\n<p>Edit:\nIs it possible to steal the foreign canvas handle and set it to my own canvas? So the foreign application wouldn't draw anymore to its canvas but to my spoofed one. By this way I could override the <code>drawText()<\/code> method easily in my application.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 8605089,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "winapi",
            "canvas",
            "getmessage"
        ],
        "score": 3,
        "accepted_answer_id": 8684788,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 1090,
        "last_edit_date": 1324564880
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/iYiuI.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 276592,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 570118,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/570118/wolfgang-kuehn",
