            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1325285122,
            "creation_date": 1325285122,
            "body": "<p>Use Java Instrumentation to inject code into drawString(), for example with Javassist.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can combine code from <a href=\"http://isisblogs.poly.edu/2011/12/25/java-dynamic-instrumentation-1/\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a> to inject your code with <code>insertBefore<\/code> and <a href=\"http://today.java.net/pub/a/today/2008/04/24/add-logging-at-class-load-time-with-instrumentation.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">there<\/a> to activate the transformation in the <code>premain<\/code> method.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8684788,
            "question_id": 8605089
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7afeb4d1993dc25c6028646840e4868a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 333768,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 659804,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/659804/ernest-friedman-hill",
                "reputation": 81908,
                "display_name": "Ernest Friedman-Hill",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1324563952,
            "creation_date": 1324563952,
            "body": "<p>It would be easy enough to write your own subclass of <code>Graphics2D<\/code> and have the drawing done on that; your subclass could override <code>drawString()<\/code> to do whatever you'd like. I would probably write the implementation as a wrapper which forwarded all method calls to another instance specified as a constructor argument, as that way your subclass could be used to directly write to the screen. Be sure to implement <code>create()<\/code> to return a new instance of your subclass, of course.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 8605234,
            "question_id": 8605089
        }
    ],
